      • getFlag

        public boolean getFlag()
        This method reads the flag value. This is a generic attribute. The meaning of the flag needs to be defined by the JavaDoc of the accessor to get the flag instance.
        NOTE:
        This method determines if the flag is true for all FlagModifiers.
        Specified by:
        getFlag in interface AttributeReadFlag
        Specified by:
        getFlag in interface AttributeReadFlagAdvanced
        Overrides:
        getFlag in class AbstractFlagAdvanced
        Returns:
        true if all aggregated flags are true and all parents have the same flag set to true.
